Node.Notes: He causes my soul/life to return in sense of restore vitality/vigor/strength.
Uncertain. Traditionally translated "the shadow of death/death's shadow." Elsewhere may simply mean "darkness/deep darkness" (see ps44:19; 107:10; Job 3:5; 10:22; 12:22; 16:16; Isa 9:2).
Part of prescribed etiquette for welcoming/honoring a guest.
A gesture of generosity from the host..
